@node The Command-Line Client
@chapter The Command-Line Client
@cindex CLI
@cindex ownsona command

OwnSona ships with a small standalone CLI under @file{cli/} for
reading from and writing to the memory store from the terminal.  It's
useful for scripting, ad-hoc edits, and bulk-loading facts.  Written in
portable C; builds on Linux, macOS, and Windows (MSYS2 UCRT64) with one
runtime dependency: libcurl.

Each MCP tool maps to a subcommand:

@example
ownsona add    "<text>"           # remember
ownsona query  "<question>"       # recall
ownsona search "<substring>"      # text_search
ownsona list                      # list_memories
ownsona update <id> "<text>"      # update_memory
ownsona confirm <id>              # confirm
ownsona forget <id>               # forget
ownsona prompt "<user prompt>"    # build_context_prompt
ownsona import FILE               # remember_batch (JSON or one-per-line)
ownsona teach  FILE               # extract facts from prose via an LLM
@end example

The @code{teach} subcommand is covered in its own chapter
(@pxref{The teach Workflow}).  The others are documented here.

